00:30:28,389 --> 00:30:30,466
He practically blew him.

253
00:30:37,984 --> 00:30:39,264
Coroner just called.

254
00:30:39,527 --> 00:30:42,019
They found chocolate
in the girl's stomach.

255
00:30:42,406 --> 00:30:44,861
We got wrappers in the cab
of the lndian's truck.

256
00:30:45,117 --> 00:30:46,528
Deputy!

257
00:30:48,287 --> 00:30:49,533
There you go.

258
00:30:53,669 --> 00:30:55,578
-Come on, Toby.
-Goddamn it!

259
00:31:00,218 --> 00:31:03,670
Come on, walk like a policeman, Toby.
You're a policeman now.

260
00:31:06,517 --> 00:31:07,797
Okay to use this phone?

261
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:10,848
-Yeah, go ahead.
-Christ!

262
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:19,820
-You fish the lakes up here, l'm told?
-Yeah.

263
00:31:20,366 --> 00:31:22,323
Anglers haven't been doing much.

264
00:31:22,577 --> 00:31:26,824
The spear houses have hit pretty heavy.
lt could be the snow cover.

265
00:31:27,082 --> 00:31:28,541
Could be that.

266
00:31:28,792 --> 00:31:30,453
What about the--?

267
00:31:32,255 --> 00:31:35,375
He's got my gun! He's got my gun!

268
00:31:37,260 --> 00:31:40,926
-Tell me when, Jerry.
-Drop it!

269
00:31:41,182 --> 00:31:42,724
-He's got Hamilton!
-Let go!

270
00:31:42,975 --> 00:31:44,968
-Freeze!
-Put it down, Toby!

271
00:31:45,895 --> 00:31:47,354
No!

272
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:51,523
Don't shoot me! Please don't!
Don't shoot me!

273
00:31:51,777 --> 00:31:53,854
-Toby, put it down!
-l kill the girl!

274
00:31:54,113 --> 00:31:55,145
Goddamn it. No!

275
00:32:03,416 --> 00:32:06,168
-Oh, God.
-ls everyone okay?

276
00:32:06,419 --> 00:32:07,795
-Get a roll call!
-Fitz!

277
00:32:08,046 --> 00:32:08,828
l'm on it.

278
00:32:09,089 --> 00:32:12,209
-Fitz!
-Hamilton! Michael!

279
00:32:12,468 --> 00:32:13,713
Are you hit?

280
00:32:15,263 --> 00:32:17,588
-l don't think so.
-Oh, Jesus.

281
00:32:17,849 --> 00:32:20,305
All right. Oh, Mike, you all right?

282
00:32:23,647 --> 00:32:25,889
Oh, my God.

283
00:32:28,361 --> 00:32:29,939
-Jesus Christ.
-You all right?

284
00:32:30,655 --> 00:32:32,565
-Get an ambulance. Do it.
-Right.

285
00:32:33,158 --> 00:32:37,572
-l thought he was gonna kill me.
-You're all right! You're okay.

286
00:32:43,962 --> 00:32:45,671
What's that, the bullet?

287
00:32:47,008 --> 00:32:48,585
His tooth.

288
00:32:55,142 --> 00:32:58,013
Gate 42. They'll be boarding
in about half an hour.

289
00:32:58,271 --> 00:33:01,474
-ls that Concourse E?
-Yes, it is, sir.

290
00:33:01,733 --> 00:33:03,773
-Thank you very much.
-You're welcome.

291
00:33:04,027 --> 00:33:05,819
Next in line, please.

292
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,901
Hi, how are you folks today?

293
00:33:10,159 --> 00:33:12,615
Thank you.
Going to Cabo San Lucas today.

294
00:33:12,871 --> 00:33:16,952
Wadenah had been previously convicted
of similar crimes and was on parole.

295
00:33:17,209 --> 00:33:20,294
Regarding the suicide of
the suspect while in custody...

296
00:33:20,546 --> 00:33:23,464
... State's Attorney Paul Ross
has organized a committee...

297
00:33:23,717 --> 00:33:27,086
... to look into the tactics
of the Becker County Sheriff's office.

298
00:33:30,224 --> 00:33:31,220
You okay?

299
00:33:33,686 --> 00:33:34,718
Yes, thank you.

300
00:33:35,355 --> 00:33:37,763
Sheriff's investigators
worked in concert...

301
00:33:38,025 --> 00:33:40,812
... with Reno homicide detectives
for several hours...

302
00:33:41,070 --> 00:33:46,065
...piecing together the trail that led
to the brisk apprehension of Wadenah.

303
00:33:46,326 --> 00:33:49,031
Authorities here,
while understandably disturbed...

304
00:33:49,288 --> 00:33:52,075
...by the brief hostage-taking
of one of their deputies...

305
00:33:52,333 --> 00:33:54,041
...are taking some comfort...

306
00:33:54,878 --> 00:33:58,413
. . .in the swift justice of this
very dramatic evening.

307
00:34:04,931 --> 00:34:09,510
Yet, while an investigation is
underway, the consensus seems clear.

308
00:34:09,770 --> 00:34:13,685
Wadenah confessed after being
identified by the young snowmobiler.

309
00:34:13,941 --> 00:34:16,859
His suicide brought a brutal end....

310
00:34:17,112 --> 00:34:21,774
Final boarding call, Northwest
flight 1607 to Cabo San Lucas.

311
00:35:45,505 --> 00:35:46,834
Customer, Oliver!

312
00:35:54,057 --> 00:35:55,551
-Morning.
-Morning.

313
00:35:55,809 --> 00:35:59,510
Nice day today. Can we help you
with anything in particular?

314
00:35:59,772 --> 00:36:01,052
Well, actually, there is.

315
00:36:01,524 --> 00:36:06,815
l'm looking for a person.
Annalise, or Anna-Lisa Hansen.

316
00:36:07,239 --> 00:36:11,569
Yes. She would live above
the electric store.

317
00:36:12,203 --> 00:36:16,450
That would be a small unit.
lt's two doors down to your left.

318
00:36:17,959 --> 00:36:22,622
And if l were you, l'd go around
the corner and take the stairs up.

319
00:36:23,048 --> 00:36:26,050
You shouldn't have
any trouble finding her.

320
00:36:26,469 --> 00:36:28,129
lf you don't, come back.

321
00:36:28,388 --> 00:36:30,096
Thank you. l appreciate it.

322
00:36:30,349 --> 00:36:31,843
You're welcome.

323
00:36:44,865 --> 00:36:48,032
So, what is it that you need to know?

324
00:36:50,163 --> 00:36:53,248
Well, l'm trying to fill in the gaps.

325
00:36:55,377 --> 00:36:58,213
Fit all the pieces
together, Mrs. Hansen.

326
00:36:58,464 --> 00:37:01,382
lf you could remember anything. . .

327
00:37:01,635 --> 00:37:04,719
. . .from when you were interviewed. . .

328
00:37:05,472 --> 00:37:07,596
. . .anything in particular
that might. . . .

329
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:12,016
lt was Wednesday and she never came.

330
00:37:12,272 --> 00:37:15,558
They said that she
never got on the bus. . .

331
00:37:15,818 --> 00:37:18,274
. . .never even made it to the school.

332
00:37:18,529 --> 00:37:22,148
l assumed that she'd gone home.

333
00:37:28,708 --> 00:37:30,997
What was she like?

334
00:37:32,212 --> 00:37:35,166
What were your Wednesdays
with Ginny. . .

335
00:37:35,424 --> 00:37:36,622
. . .what were they like?

336
00:37:37,968 --> 00:37:41,836
Oh, she would come in
with her little knapsack. . .

337
00:37:42,098 --> 00:37:45,550
. . .and plop it on the floor.

338
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:48,643
Give me a kiss on my cheek.

339
00:37:48,897 --> 00:37:51,389
Big kiss, always my left cheek.

340
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:57,986
And then, it was time for work.

341
00:37:59,785 --> 00:38:02,490
The moment she would sit
at the piano. . .

342
00:38:03,623 --> 00:38:05,580
. . .we were all business.

343
00:38:07,335 --> 00:38:09,293
And l would give her. . .

344
00:38:09,546 --> 00:38:14,886
. . .her lesson just the same
as all my other pupils.

345
00:38:16,304 --> 00:38:19,555
And it was no ''Grandma'' this
or ''Grandma'' that.

346
00:38:25,064 --> 00:38:27,390
But the moment we were done. . .

347
00:38:27,651 --> 00:38:29,193
. . .she was my Ginny again.

348
00:38:32,573 --> 00:38:35,527
How could God be so greedy?

349
00:38:36,577 --> 00:38:38,202
Ma'am, l. . . .

350
00:38:45,963 --> 00:38:47,873
And after the lesson?

351
00:38:49,843 --> 00:38:51,302
Cookies.

352
00:38:52,888 --> 00:38:56,507
We would have cookies,
if l'd baked them.

353
00:38:56,976 --> 00:39:00,227
Sometimes l would send her down
to the Land of Christmas. . .

354
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:04,146
. . .the store downstairs,
for candy or ice cream.

355
00:39:04,443 --> 00:39:08,773
She would eat her sweets
and l would read to her.

356
00:39:09,949 --> 00:39:12,108
She loved Andersen.

357
00:39:13,286 --> 00:39:14,401
Who?

358
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:18,948
Do you know what he wrote
in his story ''The Angel''?

359
00:39:20,587 --> 00:39:21,749
No.

360
00:39:26,260 --> 00:39:27,256
Here.

361
00:39:32,559 --> 00:39:36,687
''Whenever a good child dies. . .

362
00:39:36,939 --> 00:39:39,347
. . .an angel of God. . .

363
00:39:39,609 --> 00:39:42,693
. . .comes down from Heaven. . .

364
00:39:42,946 --> 00:39:45,900
. . .and takes the child in his arms.

365
00:39:46,742 --> 00:39:50,574
And spreads out his great white wings.

366
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:53,453
And flies with her. . .

367
00:39:54,292 --> 00:39:56,962
. . .over all the places. . .

368
00:39:57,212 --> 00:40:00,249
. . .that she loved during her life.

369
00:40:01,425 --> 00:40:04,427
And then, the child carries. . .

370
00:40:07,516 --> 00:40:10,303
. . .a large handful of flowers. . .

371
00:40:11,145 --> 00:40:13,054
. . .up to God. ''

372
00:40:22,074 --> 00:40:23,355
Beautiful.

373
00:40:41,346 --> 00:40:42,841
What's your name?

374
00:40:44,058 --> 00:40:46,514
Becky. Becky Fiske.

375
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:49,809
And you were Ginny's best friend?

376
00:40:51,024 --> 00:40:52,768
We sat together.

377
00:40:53,402 --> 00:40:54,683
She died.

378
00:40:55,821 --> 00:40:58,028
Yeah. l know.

379
00:41:00,243 --> 00:41:05,072
Her grandmother told me
that Ginny liked to tell stories.

380
00:41:06,959 --> 00:41:08,454
Sometimes.

381
00:41:11,464 --> 00:41:13,422
What kind of stories?

382
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:17,251
Ginny knew a giant.

383
00:41:18,473 --> 00:41:19,753
Giant?

384
00:41:21,893 --> 00:41:23,056
Really?

385
00:41:24,021 --> 00:41:28,600
He was as big as a mountain
and gave her porcupines.

386
00:41:29,110 --> 00:41:31,981
She called him ''The Wizard. ''

387
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:34,983
Ginny made a picture of him.

388
00:41:39,247 --> 00:41:41,572
Ginny drew a picture of a giant?

389
00:41:42,751 --> 00:41:44,293
Can l see it?

390
00:41:44,586 --> 00:41:46,626
lt's on the wall in the hallway.

391
00:41:47,005 --> 00:41:48,963
We put Ginny's picture--

392
00:41:52,804 --> 00:41:54,263
l gotta go.

393
00:43:05,262 --> 00:43:06,971
Jean, hold my calls.

394
00:43:38,634 --> 00:43:41,090
You were supposed to be
fishing in Mexico.

395
00:43:44,224 --> 00:43:45,932
l know, Stan.

396
00:43:47,102 --> 00:43:49,179
l went to the airport.

397
00:43:49,939 --> 00:43:52,181
l heard the boarding announcement.

398
00:43:54,236 --> 00:43:56,110
l just didn't feel right.

399
00:43:57,406 --> 00:44:02,282
Something went off.
l need more time on this.

400
00:44:05,373 --> 00:44:08,291
You want me to reopen a case
because you got a hunch?

401
00:44:11,047 --> 00:44:14,381
No offense, but you're retired.
You don't work here anymore.

402
00:44:18,222 --> 00:44:19,597
Okay.

403
00:44:19,974 --> 00:44:21,717
l know, Stan.

404
00:44:22,059 --> 00:44:26,521
l know. But could you run it
through the system for me anyway?

405
00:44:26,773 --> 00:44:28,565
You know, just a standard query.

406
00:44:28,817 --> 00:44:31,772
Similar crimes, profile, victims.

407
00:44:33,781 --> 00:44:34,979
Could you?

408
00:44:36,659 --> 00:44:38,070
Say, for. . .

409
00:44:45,002 --> 00:44:47,410
. . .the last 10, 12 years.

410
00:44:48,131 --> 00:44:49,709
Could you, Stan?

411
00:44:57,892 --> 00:44:59,173
Please?

412
00:45:55,042 --> 00:45:57,533
This is eight years ago
when this happened.

413
00:45:58,838 --> 00:46:03,334
l'm on the job only six months
when this very big deal goes down.

414
00:46:03,885 --> 00:46:06,293
Talk about baptism by fire.

415
00:46:06,847 --> 00:46:08,638
And to top off everything else. . .

416
00:46:08,891 --> 00:46:10,469
. . .it was in the summer season.

417
00:46:10,726 --> 00:46:13,015
''Politics of tourism''
and all that nonsense.

418
00:46:13,271 --> 00:46:17,684
So we all feel the pressure to make
the bogeyman of it all disappear.

419
00:46:17,943 --> 00:46:20,399
The brass were pretty clear
in the presumption. . .

420
00:46:20,654 --> 00:46:22,778
. . .that it was one
of those festival-goers. . .

421
00:46:23,032 --> 00:46:26,366
. . .which seemed like, you know,
a pretty good bet.

422
00:46:26,620 --> 00:46:30,120
And a good way to diffuse
the kind of panic that you get. . .

423
00:46:30,374 --> 00:46:33,245
. . .when they feel that there's
a bogeyman amongst them.

424
00:46:33,503 --> 00:46:34,997
So we all figured. . .

425
00:46:35,255 --> 00:46:40,131
. . .and l do feel accurately,
that's why we never did catch him.

426
00:46:42,263 --> 00:46:45,679
The odds were on a perpetrator. . .

427
00:46:45,934 --> 00:46:49,849
. . .who'd cleared the county
before the body was ever found.

428
00:46:50,981 --> 00:46:52,262
Yeah.

429
00:46:54,652 --> 00:46:56,894
Look at the slit in that neck.

430
00:46:57,155 --> 00:46:59,064
l don't know, but for me. . .

431
00:47:01,410 --> 00:47:03,118
. . .it's like being in a movie.

432
00:47:04,288 --> 00:47:07,823
This stuff just doesn't bother me
like it does some people. You?

433
00:47:10,253 --> 00:47:11,878
Luanne Rotze.

434
00:47:12,130 --> 00:47:14,088
A little 10-year-old girl.

435
00:47:14,633 --> 00:47:17,670
Real little.
l mean, real small for her age.

436
00:47:17,929 --> 00:47:19,471
You know what, though?

437
00:47:19,973 --> 00:47:22,595
As horrible as that
kind of thing is. . .

438
00:47:22,851 --> 00:47:25,224
. . .l got an adrenaline rush
being part of it.

439
00:47:25,896 --> 00:47:28,933
l don't know if that's bad,
but, hey, don't hurt me.

440
00:47:29,192 --> 00:47:30,983
That's just the way it hit me.

441
00:47:31,653 --> 00:47:34,227
Nothing like it
ever happened before here.

442
00:47:34,865 --> 00:47:37,902
By the way, nothing like it
ever happened since.

443
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:39,536
l think that says a lot.

444
00:47:41,498 --> 00:47:44,665
-You mind if l keep this one?
-l couldn't let you do that.

445
00:47:45,002 --> 00:47:46,627
We always like to be of help. . .

446
00:47:46,879 --> 00:47:49,964
. . .but, strictly technically,
the case is still open.

447
00:47:50,967 --> 00:47:53,007
Well, then, how about the report?

448
00:47:55,556 --> 00:47:57,513
l'll make you a copy. How's that?

449
00:47:58,267 --> 00:48:00,141
Sure would appreciate it.

450
00:48:00,394 --> 00:48:02,186
But keep it between us.

451
00:48:02,438 --> 00:48:05,974
l'm not sure what the policy is
on this kind of thing. Okay?

452
00:48:06,860 --> 00:48:08,403
My lips are sealed.

453
00:48:10,239 --> 00:48:11,615
Lucy!

454
00:48:12,492 --> 00:48:15,612
A young horse is like a woman.
Can't predict what they'll do.

455
00:48:15,871 --> 00:48:17,246
They're crazy.

456
00:48:24,589 --> 00:48:26,499
Excuse me. Sir?

457
00:48:26,758 --> 00:48:27,707
Sir?

458
00:48:27,968 --> 00:48:32,180
l wonder if you could tell me where
a man named James Olstad might be?

459
00:48:32,431 --> 00:48:34,508
Olstad's not a patient here.

460
00:48:35,643 --> 00:48:37,850
Well, l believe he's
the custodian, sir.

461
00:48:38,105 --> 00:48:40,430
ln the building, mopping?
He's not a patient.

462
00:48:40,691 --> 00:48:42,814
-Mopping in the building?
-Not a patient.

463
00:49:07,311 --> 00:49:08,854
James Olstad?

464
00:49:15,112 --> 00:49:18,564
l'm Jerry Black.
l'm a police detective.

465
00:49:18,825 --> 00:49:23,368
l'd just like to talk to you
about your daughter.

466
00:49:25,749 --> 00:49:27,125
What daughter?

467
00:49:29,045 --> 00:49:33,292
You did have a daughter that went
missing three years ago, didn't you?

468
00:49:35,093 --> 00:49:39,590
Did you come here to tell me
that something happened to her?

469
00:49:39,849 --> 00:49:40,845
No, sir. lt was--

470
00:49:41,100 --> 00:49:43,177
Did you find her dead or something?

471
00:49:44,980 --> 00:49:47,138
No. No, sir.

472
00:49:48,525 --> 00:49:50,732
We're still trying to find her.

473
00:49:54,824 --> 00:49:57,280
Anything you might tell me about her?

474
00:49:57,536 --> 00:49:59,363
Could you describe her?

475
00:50:04,043 --> 00:50:05,835
She must be--

476
00:50:10,217 --> 00:50:12,376
She must be different now.

477
00:50:17,976 --> 00:50:19,850
She was so pretty.

478
00:50:29,156 --> 00:50:31,528
l miss her so much!

479
00:50:37,207 --> 00:50:40,742
We just used to, like,
hold each other.

480
00:50:43,881 --> 00:50:46,669
l was supposed to take care of her.

481
00:50:46,926 --> 00:50:50,046
She was my little girl, you know?

482
00:50:50,555 --> 00:50:52,180
l just--

483
00:51:02,861 --> 00:51:04,735
l had my little girl.

484
00:51:08,451 --> 00:51:10,278
Where is my baby?

485
00:51:12,122 --> 00:51:15,622
The break is Monash County.
Eight years ago, we got a homicide.

486
00:51:16,085 --> 00:51:17,034
Same M.O.

487
00:51:17,295 --> 00:51:21,542
Exact same victim profile
description as the Ginny Larsen case.

488
00:51:22,342 --> 00:51:25,094
l interviewed a local officer
for the particulars.

489
00:51:25,554 --> 00:51:30,264
Little blonde girl, 10 years old,
sexual assault, throat slit.

490
00:51:30,894 --> 00:51:33,978
The photos show that
she was wearing a red dress.

491
00:51:35,899 --> 00:51:40,895
Detectives out at Morehead covered
this case. The case is still open.

492
00:51:41,155 --> 00:51:43,279
At the time of the murders. . .

493
00:51:43,617 --> 00:51:46,903
. . .Toby Wadenah was
in Stillwater Penitentiary. . .

494
00:51:47,162 --> 00:51:49,451
. . .doing time on his
own rape conviction.

495
00:51:49,707 --> 00:51:52,245
-He couldn't have done it.
-He shot himself.

496
00:51:52,502 --> 00:51:54,411
-What more--
-You told him what he did.

497
00:51:54,671 --> 00:51:57,838
Let's calm down, see what Jerry's got.
You got something?

498
00:51:58,092 --> 00:52:00,630
And there's more. More.

499
00:52:00,886 --> 00:52:02,760
Here. See here?

500
00:52:03,014 --> 00:52:07,641
This is the Larsen murder. This is
the Monash County girl. And here:

501
00:52:08,395 --> 00:52:10,222
Here, you see this pattern?

502
00:52:10,523 --> 00:52:14,022
Three years ago, l got a girl gone
missing, Cathy Olstad.

503
00:52:14,277 --> 00:52:17,860
