00:59:06,294 --> 00:59:07,574
Good morning.

561
00:59:09,548 --> 00:59:11,505
l'll have a pack of lights.

562
00:59:16,848 --> 00:59:17,797
That the owner?

563
00:59:18,475 --> 00:59:19,637
My daddy.

564
00:59:21,478 --> 00:59:22,807
What can l do for you?

565
00:59:24,398 --> 00:59:26,972
l was just having a look around.

566
00:59:27,985 --> 00:59:30,109
How long you had this place?

567
00:59:31,239 --> 00:59:32,817
Thirty years.

568
00:59:35,077 --> 00:59:37,070
Ever think about selling it?

569
00:59:37,830 --> 00:59:38,945
No.

570
00:59:40,291 --> 00:59:45,037
Well, what would it take to get
you to think about selling?

571
00:59:45,673 --> 00:59:46,918
lt's not for sale.

572
00:59:50,553 --> 00:59:52,213
l'll tell you what.

573
00:59:54,391 --> 00:59:57,926
l'll give you my number
over where l'm staying. . .

574
00:59:58,187 --> 01:00:01,557
. . .at Thompson's Sugar Bush Resort.

575
01:00:01,858 --> 01:00:03,767
l don't mean to be pushy but. . .

576
01:00:04,361 --> 01:00:06,270
. . .if you'd think about it. . . .

577
01:00:07,364 --> 01:00:11,197
l'll wait to hear from you over at
Thompson's, if it's all right.

578
01:00:11,995 --> 01:00:15,079
-Been a pleasure.
-Thanks for coming in.

579
01:00:15,832 --> 01:00:17,541
Nice place.

580
01:00:41,153 --> 01:00:43,230
You didn't tell me
you were a cop!

581
01:00:43,489 --> 01:00:46,610
-Ex-cop.
-Once a cop. . . .

582
01:00:48,829 --> 01:00:50,489
l'm retired.

583
01:00:50,914 --> 01:00:53,869
What l wanted to tell you was
that Floyd Cage called.

584
01:00:54,127 --> 01:00:58,374
The fellow with the gas station.
He says he wants to talk to you.

585
01:00:59,466 --> 01:01:01,126
l see they're biting.

586
01:01:02,261 --> 01:01:05,179
You bet. Sure does look like it.

587
01:01:05,431 --> 01:01:08,136
You can use the phone
up in the front cabin here.

588
01:01:08,393 --> 01:01:09,804
Thank you.

589
01:01:26,205 --> 01:01:30,749
Floyd, Jerry signed all the papers.
You're ready to go.

590
01:01:31,169 --> 01:01:33,577
l sure appreciate it.
You've done a good job.

591
01:01:33,839 --> 01:01:34,621
Good luck.

592
01:01:36,092 --> 01:01:39,627
When we get a number down in Arizona,
we'll give you a call.

593
01:01:39,888 --> 01:01:41,263
l'm going to Arizona!

594
01:01:41,515 --> 01:01:42,795
Call if you forget something. . .

595
01:01:43,058 --> 01:01:46,344
. . .or want to know where something is,
or whatever. . . .

596
01:01:46,604 --> 01:01:48,312
-Good luck to you.
-Thank you.

597
01:01:55,656 --> 01:01:57,198
l hope you'll be happy here. . .

598
01:01:57,450 --> 01:02:02,278
. . .cause you're never gonna be able
to sell it for what you paid.

599
01:02:02,956 --> 01:02:05,032
Thank you, l'll do my best.

600
01:02:05,292 --> 01:02:06,870
ls this working or what?

601
01:02:08,170 --> 01:02:11,255
l have to get a key.
l'll be right with you, thank you.

602
01:03:37,106 --> 01:03:39,183
-l'll be right with you.
-Thank you.

603
01:03:44,156 --> 01:03:45,532
What can l get you?

604
01:03:46,242 --> 01:03:47,950
Just a beer, thanks.

605
01:03:49,662 --> 01:03:51,988
You the cop
who bought the gas station?

606
01:03:52,249 --> 01:03:54,870
l'm retired from
the police department.

607
01:03:56,921 --> 01:03:59,163
And you bought Floyd's station?

608
01:04:02,427 --> 01:04:03,341
l did.

609
01:04:03,887 --> 01:04:06,924
That's a strange thing to do.
You must be an angler.

610
01:04:07,183 --> 01:04:11,015
-How'd you guess?
-Nothing else to do around here.

611
01:04:11,563 --> 01:04:13,057
Yeah.

612
01:04:36,842 --> 01:04:38,882
Sorry about that.

613
01:04:41,097 --> 01:04:44,181
These things only work half the time.

614
01:04:50,107 --> 01:04:52,147
Sign right there for me,
if you would.

615
01:04:54,445 --> 01:04:56,189
That's for you.

616
01:05:11,548 --> 01:05:12,580
Thank you and. . .

617
01:05:12,842 --> 01:05:16,045
-. . .here's your receipt.
